All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
CharacterMatrixParser
CharacterMatrixParser is a parser that parses a string input with specific format to a matrix of characters.
Color
Color is a set of predefined colors used in ColoredMatrix to output puzzle solution.
ColoredMatrix<T>
ColoredMatrix holds a generic type matrix and a Color matrix, enabling its elements to be printed with various colors defined in the color matrix.
Direction
Direction is a set of 8 equidistant discrete directions.
FileReader
FileReader is a file reader that reads a file to a string and handle any errors in the process.
InputParser
InputParser parses a raw string input to a character matrix as the puzzle and an array of strings as words to search from the puzzle.
Main
Main is the entry point of word search puzzle solver program.
Matrix<T>
Matrix is a two-dimensional array type that holds a generic type of elements.
Point
Point represents an ordered pair of integer values.
Range
Range represents an increasing integer values from a specific start value to a specific end value, inclusively.
Solver
Class Solver is a word finder for a word search puzzle.
SolveResult
SolveResult is the result of searching a word in Solver.
